For the non-baseball people:
AB = At Bats
SH = Sacrifice Bunt
SF = Sacrifice Fly
BB = Base on Balls (walks)
HBP = Hit By Pitch
IBB = Intentional Base on Balls (intentional walks)
SO = Strike Outs
H = Singles
X2H = Doubles
X3H = Triples
HR = Home Runs
The reason we are pulling extra data points like SH, SF, HBP, & IBB is because in the end we want Total At Bats. Baseball data is a little tricky in that only some plate appearances are considered an ‘At Bat’. Walks and sacrifices aren’t considered an ‘At Bat’ but for the purpose of this analysis we’ll want the total number of times they come to the plate in a season.


batting_2018 <- batting_2018 %>%
  mutate(TBB = BB + IBB + HBP,         # combine all walk types
         TAB = AB + TBB + SH + SF) %>% # create total at-bats
  select(-c(BB, IBB, HBP, SH, SF)) %>% # remove unneeded columns
  select(c(playerID, teamID, lgID, G, TAB, TBB, SO, H, X2B, X3B, HR))

head(batting_2018) %>% gt()



